public class AirlineData

AirlineData A class used to represent Airline data for use in the modify data factory patterns. Overrides checkValues() and convertBlanksToNull() from Data interface.

  • Constructor Details

    • AirlineData

      public AirlineData​(java.lang.String name, java.lang.String alias, java.lang.String iata, java.lang.String icao, java.lang.String callsign, java.lang.String country, java.lang.String active)
      Constructor for AirlineData.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the airline, cannot be null.
      alias - The alias of the airline.
      iata - The 2-letter IATA code of the airline, must be unique, may be null if not known/assigned.
      icao - The 3-letter ICAO code of the airline, must be unique, may be null if not known/assigned.
      callsign - The callsign of the airline.
      country - The country of the airline.
      active - "Y" if the airline is or has until recently been operational, "N" if it is defunct, cannot be null.
